After second stress, RWC was measured using the method described by Shivakrishna et al. (2018) [71]. In brief, fresh leaf samples (at least 0.5 g) from the control, treatment 1 (T1), and treatment 2 (T2) were immersed in 50 mL of deionized water for 12 h. Afterward, the turgid weight of each sample was recorded using a digital balance after gently removing surface water with blotting paper. The samples were dried at 80 °C until their weights became constant, after which the dry weights were recorded. ELWL was measured using the described method by McCaig et al. (1989) [72] Fresh weight of leaf samples was recorded immediately after excision. The samples were then partially dried in a drying oven at 28 °C for 6 h, followed by complete drying at 70 °C for 24 h, as described by Clarke and Townley-Smith (1986) [73]. ELWL was computed using the following formula:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
